  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bca\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bae\u0bbf\u0b9f \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "President Ranil refused to sign",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Today (31), President Ranil Wickremesinghe announced to the High Court through the Attorney General that he will not sign the execution of the death sentence.",
        "Former President Maithripala Sirisena had decided in 2019 to carry out the sentence of four drug-related convicts sentenced to death.",
        "The fundamental rights petitions filed seeking quashing of the decision were heard by Justices Vijith Mallalkoda, L.D.P. It was taken up for consideration today (31), in the presence of a panel comprising Tehiteniya and Murtu Fernando.",
        "At that time, Additional Solicitor General Nerin Pulle, appearing on behalf of the Attorney General, announced the above decision of President Ranil.",
        "The Additional Solicitor General informed the House that when the Attorney General questioned the President on this matter, the President said that he would not sign the execution of the death sentence.",
        "It was pointed out in the forum that the President had informed the Attorney General to announce his decision when the petitions in this regard are taken up for consideration in the High Court.",
        "The government has taken a decision in principle not to implement the death penalty and there is no change in that decision.",
        "Following this, Justice Vijith Malalkoda informed the petitioners to inform the petitioners in the next session whether there is an opportunity to proceed with the petitions, and fixed February 23 as the date for consideration of the petition."
      ],
